race.comment: INFINITE PRINCE (7) turned in a fine effort to score by 1.1 lengths at today's track and distance last time out to continue his outstanding recent form. Finds a tougher race but this looks well within his grasp. The well-related WHODARESWINS (3) (half to G2 winner Carrara) was well fancied last start over 1200m at Charleville when third, beaten 7 lengths. Robert Faehr has been in the money at the last four rides and rates a leading contender. YALLA (4) had been in sparkling form winning two on end before missing the frame last start over 1600m at Cloncurry. Has good early toe so she should be handy in the run. One of the main contenders. MEGHAN (9) improved sharply last time out to score by 4 lengths over 1400m at Cloncurry a week-and-a-half ago. Well placed to feature in the finish again.
